abstract: Michael Novogratz, the former Fortress executive, told Bloomberg that he was shelving plans for a cryptocurrency hedge fund and said bitcoin will fall to $8,000.
snippet: Michael Novogratz, the former Fortress executive, told Bloomberg that he was shelving plans for a cryptocurrency hedge fund and said bitcoin will fall to $8,000.

abstract: The $20 million agreement over business practices in China comes a year after William Ackman’s hedge fund closed its bearish bet.
snippet: The $20 million agreement over business practices in China comes a year after William Ackman’s hedge fund closed its bearish bet.
lead_paragraph: Herbalife, a nutritional supplement company that was once the focus of attacks by a well-known hedge fund manager, reached a settlement on Friday with securities regulators over allegations it misled investors about its business practices in China.

abstract: The activist investor William A. Ackman has unloaded his remaining positions in the company — a bet that at one time had been valued at $1 billion by his Pershing Square Capital Management.
snippet: The activist investor William A. Ackman has unloaded his remaining positions in the company — a bet that at one time had been valued at $1 billion by his Pershing Square Capital Management.
lead_paragraph: William A. Ackman has officially hoisted the white flag in his boisterous and costly five-year campaign against Herbalife, the nutritional food supplement company, which he claimed was an outright fraud.

abstract: A couple break up, but remain together, frustratingly, because of the husband’s financial woes.
snippet: A couple break up, but remain together, frustratingly, because of the husband’s financial woes.
lead_paragraph: The Belgian director Joachim Lafosse’s “After Love” is an irritating movie about irritating people. The married Boris and Marie are breaking up but for economic reasons are still sharing the same living space (to which the entire movie is confined; good thing there’s an outdoor patio). They have lovely twin daughters in front of whom they mostly argue — vehemently and with little regard for how these displays will affect the girls. Money is an issue; Marie comes from affluence, while Boris, a contractor who refers to himself as an architect, rarely has any. He incessantly confronts Marie over the labor he’s put into their apartment.

abstract: A documentary about the Syrian civil war focuses on members of a search-and-rescue group that digs for bodies after buildings have been bombed.
snippet: A documentary about the Syrian civil war focuses on members of a search-and-rescue group that digs for bodies after buildings have been bombed.
lead_paragraph: After President Bashar al-Assad of Syria was accused of using sarin gas in an attack on his country’s people, and images of dead children shocked the world, a missile strike on a military airfield ordered by President Trump was celebrated in some of the United States media. The conventional wisdom held that standing up to Mr. Assad would teach a lesson. More than one journalist invoked the notion of beauty in describing the attack.

abstract: Tim Lee, an obscure economist who writes an investment newsletter, predicted that Turkey’s currency would collapse. Now, he foresees a broader financial crisis.
snippet: Tim Lee, an obscure economist who writes an investment newsletter, predicted that Turkey’s currency would collapse. Now, he foresees a broader financial crisis.
lead_paragraph: For the past seven years, Tim Lee has been warning that a financial crisis in Turkey would set off a wider calamity in global markets.

abstract: The often irreverent French director François Ozon gets serious with a fact-based story about a group of men who were childhood victims of a pedophile priest.
snippet: The often irreverent French director François Ozon gets serious with a fact-based story about a group of men who were childhood victims of a pedophile priest.
lead_paragraph: For a member of the clergy to sexually violate a child is one of the most stark and cruel betrayals imaginable. That an institution would prevaricate and dissemble about these betrayals rather than take immediate, decisive action to pursue justice and provide restitution creates a greater betrayal. After years of such actions, betrayal reaches a near-unimaginable level.

abstract: The stock market continued to plunge Monday, as investors were unnerved by the unpredictable White House. Stocks are now down 4 percent this year.

lead_paragraph: The Trump Bump is becoming the Trump Slump.

abstract: As a candidate, Donald Trump warned about the fragile economy and the overinflated stock market. As president, he takes credit for every record high.
snippet: As a candidate, Donald Trump warned about the fragile economy and the overinflated stock market. As president, he takes credit for every record high.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As America’s stock markets have reached record highs, they have had few louder cheerleaders than President Trump.

abstract: Zakiyyah Alexander’s ambitious play leaves the viewer wanting more, but several other works register as contrived or wan.
snippet: Zakiyyah Alexander’s ambitious play leaves the viewer wanting more, but several other works register as contrived or wan.
lead_paragraph: Most one-act plays have, by default, a tight focus: between two and four characters, unity of time and place. “The Good Muslim,” on the other hand, ambitiously moves seven characters through a fast-food prep area, a porch, the subway and even virtual reality. Zakiyyah Alexander’s piece — part of the final installment of Ensemble Studio Theater’s annual one-act play series — also tackles assimilation, racism and sexism.

abstract: The central bank has embraced an easy monetary policy, but it has left the markets wondering if the economy is in trouble.
snippet: The central bank has embraced an easy monetary policy, but it has left the markets wondering if the economy is in trouble.
lead_paragraph: The Federal Reserve gave Wall Street just about everything it wanted, helping to make the first three months of 2019 a great time to be in stocks and bonds.

abstract: The career of an eclectic musician spanned decades before what turned out to be a final show in Atlanta, a concert in honor of his birthday.
snippet: The career of an eclectic musician spanned decades before what turned out to be a final show in Atlanta, a concert in honor of his birthday.
lead_paragraph: Bruce Hampton, a singer, guitarist, songwriter and bandleader known for his energetic, eccentric style and widely regarded as the granddaddy of the jam-band scene, died on Monday in Atlanta. He was 70.

abstract: The central bank’s Governing Council has become more optimistic about the eurozone economy, offering a hint at winding down stimulus measures.
snippet: The central bank’s Governing Council has become more optimistic about the eurozone economy, offering a hint at winding down stimulus measures.
lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — With crucial elections approaching in France, the European Central Bank opted on Thursday against rocking the boat, leaving its monetary policy unchanged for the 19 nations using the euro.

abstract: Elon Musk’s electric-car company began the year with high expectations. But it has confronted a series of problems and a loss of investor confidence.
snippet: Elon Musk’s electric-car company began the year with high expectations. But it has confronted a series of problems and a loss of investor confidence.
lead_paragraph: Tesla’s Model 3 electric sedan was heralded this year by Consumer Reports as the most satisfying car on the market. Then owners started to complain that cars had arrived with cracked windows, leaks or unreliable video screens. In some places, Tesla turned to outside body shops to repair scratches and other paint defects before cars were delivered to customers.

abstract: Securities regulators and the chief executive of Tesla came up with a new agreement about when Mr. Musk’s social media posts must be reviewed by a lawyer.
snippet: Securities regulators and the chief executive of Tesla came up with a new agreement about when Mr. Musk’s social media posts must be reviewed by a lawyer.
lead_paragraph: If it was not already clear, securities regulators are giving Elon Musk, the chief executive of Tesla, a laundry list of things he cannot riff about on Twitter.

abstract: National Trust properties, grand sites often bequeathed by Britons who can no longer afford them, are a surprisingly child-friendly option for getaways.
snippet: National Trust properties, grand sites often bequeathed by Britons who can no longer afford them, are a surprisingly child-friendly option for getaways.
lead_paragraph: In that exhilarating and sleep deprived first year of parenthood, one of my fondest memories is the summer afternoon my husband and I spent with our then six-month-old son touring Melford Hall in the countryside dotted by farms in Suffolk, roughly two hours northeast of London.

abstract: The bond markets are getting fussy.
snippet: The bond markets are getting fussy.
lead_paragraph: The S&P 500 suffered its worst single-day drop in a month yesterday, with tech stocks hard hit. But the big story is in bonds, where yields surged (and prices fell) as investors worried that the Fed wasn’t, well, worried enough.

abstract: The company encountered supply-chain problems and investor concern after its initial public offering last year gave it a huge market value.
snippet: The company encountered supply-chain problems and investor concern after its initial public offering last year gave it a huge market value.
lead_paragraph: Shares of Rivian, the electric-vehicle maker that went public last year with big ambitions to take on Tesla and others, jumped Thursday after the company reaffirmed its production forecast for this year despite supply-chain problems.

abstract: Simply buying and holding a diversified portfolio is a time-tested strategy that has worked for many people. But there are other options.

lead_paragraph: Stocks began to swing wildly over the summer, and while things have quieted down a bit, many veterans expect more turbulence ahead.

abstract: Here’s why he is still winning.
snippet: Here’s why he is still winning.
lead_paragraph: It was yet another epic failure of political punditry. Go back to the early months of Joe Biden’s presidential campaign and read what the consultants and commentators were saying about him: His support is just name recognition; he’ll fade! He’s too old! He’s running a zombie campaign! The party has moved left and he’s out of touch! He voted for the crime bill!

abstract: He enjoyed “the freedom you have as a bad guy,” which he was in scores of movie and television shows. But he branched out as his career advanced.

lead_paragraph: Rutger Hauer, the ruggedly handsome Dutch actor who brought a sinister intensity to villainous roles in “Blade Runner,” “Nighthawks,” “Buffy the Vampire Slayer” and other movies, died on Friday at his home in the Friesland province of the Netherlands. He was 75.

abstract: China’s stock market has fallen into a bear market and the currency is tumbling on worries about tariffs and China’s efforts to rein in domestic debt.
snippet: China’s stock market has fallen into a bear market and the currency is tumbling on worries about tariffs and China’s efforts to rein in domestic debt.
lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI — Months of struggling with economic problems at home and bickering with President Trump over trade are starting to take their toll on China’s financial health.

abstract: “Their product isn’t very good these days,’’ a bookmaker said of the N.F.L. and its various troubles, as bets on college football rise.
snippet: “Their product isn’t very good these days,’’ a bookmaker said of the N.F.L. and its various troubles, as bets on college football rise.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Jimmy Vaccaro has spent four decades as a bookmaker watching money move through an increasingly lucrative sports market. He is, by necessity, an astute observer of the human condition.

abstract: Market watchers are divided on whether the current slump will be prolonged or a blip, and history doesn’t offer a clear answer. Expect turbulence.
snippet: Market watchers are divided on whether the current slump will be prolonged or a blip, and history doesn’t offer a clear answer. Expect turbulence.
lead_paragraph: A year ago, in the wake of President Trump’s tax cut, euphoric investors pushed the Dow Jones industrial average past 25,000, a record. The Dow had just gained 25 percent in 2017, and the Nasdaq had leapt 28 percent. Volatility was so low that there wasn’t a single day in 2017 when the S&P 500 fluctuated more than 2 percent.

abstract: To say that we find ourselves in a dysfunctional relationship is an understatement.
snippet: To say that we find ourselves in a dysfunctional relationship is an understatement.
lead_paragraph: If, by some grievous misfortune, you should happen to have a pathological narcissist in your life — a drain on your soul, a bottomless chute of need, a roaring outboard motor of jealousies and delusions and self-regard — there’s no shortage of literature offering advice, and most of it preaches the same thing: Never take the bait. If you can disengage, by all means do; if you cannot, keep clear boundaries. Even if it means building an alligator-filled moat.

abstract: Debt needn’t be a big problem for companies with strong cash flow. But in those three industries, some companies are facing stress.
snippet: Debt needn’t be a big problem for companies with strong cash flow. But in those three industries, some companies are facing stress.
lead_paragraph: While many companies have shrewdly taken advantage of rock-bottom interest rates over the last decade, bulging debt in industries like retail, energy and telecommunications is a burden that investors may need to worry about.

abstract: Wall Street, roiled this week by the most turbulence in years, broke from a brief respite on Thursday, entering a market correction.
snippet: Wall Street, roiled this week by the most turbulence in years, broke from a brief respite on Thursday, entering a market correction.
lead_paragraph: After watching stocks march higher for nearly nine years, investors are suddenly confronting a new reality: The long, smooth ride is over. And it doesn’t feel good.

abstract: As concerns about growth and privacy issues took a toll, technology and banking stocks led a slide in Europe, and futures indicated that markets in the United States could follow.
snippet: As concerns about growth and privacy issues took a toll, technology and banking stocks led a slide in Europe, and futures indicated that markets in the United States could follow.
lead_paragraph: Apple was worth more than $1 trillion at the start of November. Now, it’s valued at $880 billion.

abstract: Markets now have echoes of the mid-2010s, when central banks around the world were holding interest rates so low investors had little choice but to buy stocks.

lead_paragraph: Bad news is cheered. Good news makes investors nervous. Welcome to Wall Street.

abstract: Russia’s financial position is stronger in the short term than many expected.
snippet: Russia’s financial position is stronger in the short term than many expected.
lead_paragraph: President Biden bragged on Twitter on March 26 that “as a result of our unprecedented sanctions, the ruble was almost immediately reduced to rubble.” It was an ill-timed tweet. The Russian currency did crash in February after sanctions were imposed, but by the time Biden exulted, it had already regained lost ground. It’s now worth about 1.2 cents, which is down from 1.3 cents before the war but well above its wartime low of less than 0.8 cents.

abstract: For years a punch line to snooty New Yorkers, New Jersey came into its own as a cultural hub in the 1990s, thanks to Lauryn Hill, Kevin Smith and “The Sopranos.”

lead_paragraph: Original headline: “No Longer the Punch-Line State; Lauryn Hill, the Sopranos and others are unapologetic New Jerseyans,” from April 1999.

abstract: When the pros and cons for stocks and the economy over the next year or two are weighed, the risks appear to be dominant, our columnist says.
snippet: When the pros and cons for stocks and the economy over the next year or two are weighed, the risks appear to be dominant, our columnist says.
lead_paragraph: Project ahead a year or two: It is much easier to make a case for a troubled stock market than for a booming one.

abstract: For years a punch line to snooty New Yorkers, New Jersey came into its own as a cultural hub in the 1990s, thanks to Lauryn Hill, Kevin Smith and “The Sopranos.”
snippet: For years a punch line to snooty New Yorkers, New Jersey came into its own as a cultural hub in the 1990s, thanks to Lauryn Hill, Kevin Smith and “The Sopranos.”
lead_paragraph: Original headline: “No Longer the Punch-Line State; Lauryn Hill, the Sopranos and others are unapologetic New Jerseyans,” from April 1999.

abstract: After a once-heady outlook, estimates for the second quarter are being revised downward, and this year is looking more and more like the last several.
snippet: After a once-heady outlook, estimates for the second quarter are being revised downward, and this year is looking more and more like the last several.
lead_paragraph: The promise of faster economic growth has become a study in the triumph of hope over experience.

abstract: Where do you go when stocks and bonds are too rich? Commodities, at least price-wise, might offer an answer despite their volatility.

abstract: Though the country faces long-term problems, like soaring debt, the government’s recent moves have reassured investors that it can stave off crises.
snippet: Though the country faces long-term problems, like soaring debt, the government’s recent moves have reassured investors that it can stave off crises.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — For those who worry about the state of the world economy, China has long been a major reason to lose sleep. Its financial system labors under a mountain of loans, while weaker growth has prompted many Chinese people and companies to move their money overseas in recent years.

abstract: With a budget surplus and plans for fixing its biggest problems, the Golden State is looking a bit more golden.
snippet: With a budget surplus and plans for fixing its biggest problems, the Golden State is looking a bit more golden.
lead_paragraph: California has been struggling. It has stumbled through the Covid-19 pandemic and recession, afflicted by wildfires, an epidemic of homelessness and stratospheric housing prices. Last year it experienced its first population decline in records going back to 1900. Its latest mess was a costly and unsuccessful campaign to recall Gov. Gavin Newsom.

abstract: He wasn’t a big-league producer. But he fell in love with a small Israeli film and spent years getting it to the stage. His musical won 10 awards on Sunday.
snippet: He wasn’t a big-league producer. But he fell in love with a small Israeli film and spent years getting it to the stage. His musical won 10 awards on Sunday.
lead_paragraph: It was almost 2 a.m. Monday when Orin Wolf, the producer of “The Band’s Visit,” stepped onto the dance floor at the Bryant Park Grill, a microphone in his left hand and a Tony Award in his right.

abstract: Hedge funds’ lackluster performance so far this year should further deflate the myth that they can excel in bull and bear markets alike.
snippet: Hedge funds’ lackluster performance so far this year should further deflate the myth that they can excel in bull and bear markets alike.
lead_paragraph: Highly paid hedge fund managers have complained for years that it’s unfair to compare their performance with the broad stock market during prolonged bullish periods. Hedge funds are designed to mitigate risk, the argument goes, and so investors in them might sacrifice some gains as markets rise while waiting for hedge funds to prove themselves in more challenging times.

abstract: With signs that the long boom in American auto sales is tapering off, the Detroit giants are eclipsed on Wall Street by the electric-vehicle upstart.
snippet: With signs that the long boom in American auto sales is tapering off, the Detroit giants are eclipsed on Wall Street by the electric-vehicle upstart.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — The record pace of auto sales in the United States is slowing down, leaving investors increasingly bearish on auto stocks.

abstract: She has written about some of our biggest modern-day conundrums: whether to have children, how to live an authentic life. With her new novel, “Pure Colour,” she considers how love and art can heal.
snippet: She has written about some of our biggest modern-day conundrums: whether to have children, how to live an authentic life. With her new novel, “Pure Colour,” she considers how love and art can heal.
lead_paragraph: In her poignant and imaginative new novel, “Pure Colour,” Sheila Heti opens with an unusual concept: Humans are bears, fish or birds.

abstract: Here’s an argument against aggressively raising interest rates to stop inflation.
snippet: Here’s an argument against aggressively raising interest rates to stop inflation.
lead_paragraph: The economist David Rosenberg says it’s not just possible but likely that the U.S. economy will fall into a recession this year, partly because, he says, the Federal Reserve will go too far in raising interest rates to fight inflation, which is at a 40-year high.

abstract: New York recycles only about a fifth of its trash, lagging behind other major cities and slowing its quest to reduce waste.
snippet: New York recycles only about a fifth of its trash, lagging behind other major cities and slowing its quest to reduce waste.
lead_paragraph: If you are a New Yorker and sort your recycling at home, as city law mandates, you probably wonder, as you rinse bottles and stack junk mail and scrub yogurt containers: Does all this effort make a difference?

abstract: Beijing is opening its financial system to foreign banks — and they have maintained their traditional openness to the Communist Party’s rule.
snippet: Beijing is opening its financial system to foreign banks — and they have maintained their traditional openness to the Communist Party’s rule.
lead_paragraph: This year has been unsettling for Chinese business. The ruling Communist Party has gone after the private sector industry by industry. The stock markets have taken a huge hit. The country’s biggest property developer is on the verge of collapse.

abstract: No president in modern times has connected his political fortunes to the stock market as much as Mr. Trump. But as shares swooned Monday, he avoided any mention of it.
snippet: No president in modern times has connected his political fortunes to the stock market as much as Mr. Trump. But as shares swooned Monday, he avoided any mention of it.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As President Trump boasted about the economy during a speech on Monday, he left out one of his favorite lines. Nowhere did he mention the skyrocketing stock market.

abstract: Liberals have to forge an effective counterattack on race.
snippet: Liberals have to forge an effective counterattack on race.
lead_paragraph: The Virginia election results should shock Democrats into confronting the powerful role that racially coded attacks play in American politics. No candidate would think of entering an election without a winning message on the economy or health care. Yet by failing to counter his opponent’s racial dog whistles, Terry McAuliffe did the equivalent, finding himself defenseless against a strategy Republicans have used to win elections for decades.

abstract: Some big employers are giving up square footage as they juggle remote work. That could devastate building owners and cities.
snippet: Some big employers are giving up square footage as they juggle remote work. That could devastate building owners and cities.
lead_paragraph: As office vacancies climb to their highest levels in decades with businesses giving up office space and embracing remote work, the real estate industry in many American cities faces a potentially grave threat.

lead_paragraph: America’s job engine has again defied jittery stock traders, bearish forecasters and blue-ribbon economists to deliver eye-catching gains and power an exceptionally resilient economy.

abstract: Economic and other indicators are making it increasingly clear that Trump’s economic dreams are unlikely to come true.
snippet: Economic and other indicators are making it increasingly clear that Trump’s economic dreams are unlikely to come true.
lead_paragraph: By any measure, 2018 was another Year of Trump. From his efforts to remake the American economy to his go-it-alone trade war to his curious pro-Putin foreign policy to the at least 17 investigations underway into his various activities, President Trump dominated the news as few of his predecessors have done. But by the end of his second year, the prospects that he would achieve his economic goals were in grave doubt as growth slowed and the stock market swooned.

abstract: Flush with cash, Facebook, Apple, Amazon, Microsoft and Google are positioned to emerge from a downturn stronger and more powerful. As usual.
snippet: Flush with cash, Facebook, Apple, Amazon, Microsoft and Google are positioned to emerge from a downturn stronger and more powerful. As usual.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Apple, Amazon, Microsoft and the parent companies of Facebook and Google have lost $2.7 trillion in value so far this year, about the annual gross domestic product of Britain.

abstract: Investors have cast the nearly relentless drumbeat of bad news aside to focus on any signs that the worst of the coronavirus pandemic might be over.
snippet: Investors have cast the nearly relentless drumbeat of bad news aside to focus on any signs that the worst of the coronavirus pandemic might be over.
lead_paragraph: Widespread economic devastation, severe unemployment and a grim prognosis for recovery have not stopped the stock market’s exuberance. And on Tuesday, that undying optimism propelled the market to a new high, pushing it past a milestone reached only six months ago, when the coronavirus was just beginning its harrowing journey across the United States.

abstract: As the pandemic accelerated the demise of some brick-and-mortar retailers, a group of investors profited handsomely from their travails.
snippet: As the pandemic accelerated the demise of some brick-and-mortar retailers, a group of investors profited handsomely from their travails.
lead_paragraph: Catie McKee was nervous. It was last October, and the 31-year-old hedge fund analyst, who had been scrutinizing the mortgages on the nation’s malls, was convinced that some of those malls would default on their loans. She and her colleagues had even bet a substantial amount of money on that likelihood.

abstract: The risks of relying economically on the Asian superpower have never seemed clearer. But as the world tries to get moving again, it needs China more than ever.
snippet: The risks of relying economically on the Asian superpower have never seemed clearer. But as the world tries to get moving again, it needs China more than ever.
lead_paragraph: As the coronavirus pandemic amplifies longstanding concerns over the world’s economic dependence on China, many countries are trying to reduce their exposure to Beijing’s brand of business.

abstract: What does Turrell, the master of light, have in common with Ad Reinhardt, the master of dark? Benches, for starters.
snippet: What does Turrell, the master of light, have in common with Ad Reinhardt, the master of dark? Benches, for starters.
lead_paragraph: A compelling new show at the Pace Gallery in Manhattan, “Ad Reinhardt: Color Out of Darkness,” comes with an unusual perk. It has been “curated by James Turrell,” as the subtitle proclaims. The prospect of Turrell, an American master of light, presiding over a show of paintings by Reinhardt, an American master of dark, has a special allure, offering not only two visions for the price of one but a glimpse at the improbable ways of inspiration.

abstract: The Securities and Exchange Commission filed a lawsuit Thursday that accused Mr. Musk, the electric-car manufacturer’s chief executive, of making false and misleading public statements.
snippet: The Securities and Exchange Commission filed a lawsuit Thursday that accused Mr. Musk, the electric-car manufacturer’s chief executive, of making false and misleading public statements.
lead_paragraph: Elon Musk, Tesla’s chief executive, was accused by federal regulators on Thursday of misleading investors with false public statements, a move that could force him out of the company’s leadership.

abstract: Investors are re-pricing the risks of the latest coronavirus variant.
snippet: Investors are re-pricing the risks of the latest coronavirus variant.
lead_paragraph: Scientists, doctors and public health officials are still assessing the danger posed by the Omicron variant of the coronavirus, but markets are already jumping to conclusions. On Friday, markets fell on fears that the fast-spreading strain of the coronavirus first detected in South Africa, and which has now been found in more than a dozen countries, could throw the global economic recovery into reverse. Many countries have banned travel from countries in Southern Africa, while Israel, Japan and Morocco closed their borders to all outside travelers.

abstract: In 1996, the activist artist found inspiration at two of his favorite museums. The discussion that followed, with a Times critic, revealed a man of his generation, whose art is as timely as ever.
snippet: In 1996, the activist artist found inspiration at two of his favorite museums. The discussion that followed, with a Times critic, revealed a man of his generation, whose art is as timely as ever.
lead_paragraph: Shuttered since March by the coronavirus pandemic, the Museum of Modern Art and the Metropolitan Museum of Art are reopening with limited visitorship, various admonitions about masks and social distancing, and several new exhibitions, among them “Jacob Lawrence: The American Struggle.” That show, at the Met, reunites the panels of a lesser-known series that the storied modernist painted during the mid-1950s, exploring themes from the American Revolution to the Westward expansion.

abstract: Thirty years ago Jean Touitou, a onetime communist agitator, traded revolution for a good life in the rag trade.
snippet: Thirty years ago Jean Touitou, a onetime communist agitator, traded revolution for a good life in the rag trade.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — There is an indelible truth about A.P.C., the willfully anonymous French fashion label that has been quietly going about its business for three decades, one that is both right and not quite right. It concerns the clothes that A.P.C. makes, and also its ambitions, the A.P.C. epithet and albatross: “This eternal thing: ‘They do basics,’” said Jean Touitou, the A.P.C. founder, sitting at his dining table, battling back his bugbear of decades. “This has been for 30 years.”
